CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F364A1774959066
OL,3,CMan told friends house was "going out
OL,4,Cwith a bang" before fatal explosion
OL,6,FA man killed in an explosion at his
OL,7,Fhome had warned friends "it's going to
OL,8,Fgo out with a bang" after learning his
OL,9,Frent would be going up.
OL,11,FDavid Howard died alongside his dog at
OL,12,Fthe terraced house on John Street in
OL,13,FWorksop on April 12 last year,
OL,14,Ffollowing news of the #80 a month hike
OL,15,Fin rent.
OL,17,FFriends told police how, on the day of
OL,18,Fthe explosion, Mr Howard had been
OL,19,Fmoody and depressed, fending off
OL,20,Fconcerns when they tried to knock on
OL,21,Fhis door and offer help.
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1         G1/8
OL,2,W,.!+.!/*%/*%,.!/*%/*%/"-$T,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BYorks News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,365,360,260,120,000,100
PN,36402
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F364A1774959066
OL,3,CMan told friends house was "going out
OL,4,Cwith a bang" before fatal explosion
OL,6,FShortly prior, Mr Howard had received
OL,7,Fa letter from his landlord Sarah
OL,8,FReilly informing him his rent - which
OL,9,Fwas mostly paid by Bassetlaw District
OL,10,FCouncil - would be going up to #540 a
OL,11,Fmonth.
OL,13,FAn inquest in Worksop on Monday heard
OL,14,Fhe had spiralled following the news
OL,15,Fand told a number of friends that
OL,16,Fafternoon that he was going to "blow
OL,17,Fthe house up", saying "you wait until
OL,18,Fthe end of the day".
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1         G2/8
OL,2,W,.!+.!/*%/*%,.!/*%/*%/"-$T,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BYorks News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,365,360,260,120,000,100
PN,36403
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F364A1774959066
OL,3,CMan told friends house was "going out
OL,4,Cwith a bang" before fatal explosion
OL,6,FGiving evidence at Monday's hearing,
OL,7,FDet Con Daniel Akehurst, of
OL,8,FNottinghamshire Police, told how
OL,9,Ffriend Shanelle Williams described him
OL,10,Fas being "in a mood and depressed",
OL,11,Fthat he had told her he had "pulled
OL,12,Fthe pipes" and that "it's going to go
OL,13,Fwith a bang."
OL,15,FFriends had said he had been upset for
OL,16,Fthree days worrying about his rent
OL,17,Fgoing up and had not been sleeping
OL,18,Fproperly, refusing their help or to
OL,19,Flet them take his dog, Roxy.
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1         G3/8
OL,2,W,.!+.!/*%/*%,.!/*%/*%/"-$T,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BYorks News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,365,360,260,120,000,100
PN,36404
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F364A1774959066
OL,3,CMan told friends house was "going out
OL,4,Cwith a bang" before fatal explosion
OL,6,FThere was no mention in the hearing
OL,7,Fwhether friends contacted emergency
OL,8,Fservices.
OL,10,FThe explosion that evening led to 200
OL,11,Fpeople being evacuated and damage was
OL,12,Fcaused to adjacent properties which
OL,13,Fneighbours said was still being dealt
OL,14,Fwith today.
OL,16,FEmergency services called to the
OL,17,Fstreet had found Mr Howard still
OL,18,Fconscious but trapped beneath rubble.
OL,19,FHe was pronounced dead later that
OL,20,Fevening.
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1         G4/8
OL,2,W,.!+.!/*%/*%,.!/*%/*%/"-$T,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BYorks News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,365,360,260,120,000,100
PN,36405
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F364A1774959066
OL,3,CMan told friends house was "going out
OL,4,Cwith a bang" before fatal explosion
OL,6,FThe cause of the explosion was listed
OL,7,Fas a gas leak from a cooker, likely
OL,8,Fignited by the capacitor of his fridge
OL,9,Fwhich had been "ripped out".
OL,11,FMr Howard's cause of death was given
OL,12,Fas asphyxiation from being trapped, as
OL,13,Fwell as heroin and cocaine use. He was
OL,14,Ffound to also have low levels of
OL,15,Falcohol in his system at the time,
OL,16,Fwhich would have contributed to "mild
OL,17,Fcognitive impairment".
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1         G5/8
OL,2,W,.!+.!/*%/*%,.!/*%/*%/"-$T,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BYorks News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,365,360,260,120,000,100
PN,36406
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F364A1774959066
OL,3,CMan told friends house was "going out
OL,4,Cwith a bang" before fatal explosion
OL,6,FSummarising, coroner Nathanael Hartley
OL,7,Ffound the explosion had been caused
OL,8,F"intentionally", but that he could not
OL,9,Fdetermine if Mr Howard had "intended
OL,10,Fto end his life at the time".
OL,12,FNearly one year on from the explosion,
OL,13,Fthe home on John Street remained
OL,14,Fsealed off ahead of reconstruction on
OL,15,FMonday. Flowers spelling out the word
OL,16,F"dad" could be seen at the site.
OL,18,FJane Revill, a neighbour, told ITV the
OL,19,Fforce of the explosion at the time
OL,20,Fcaused hinges on doors and windows to
OL,21,Fbend.
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1         G6/8
OL,2,W,.!+.!/*%/*%,.!/*%/*%/"-$T,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BYorks News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,365,360,260,120,000,100
PN,36407
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F364A1774959066
OL,3,CMan told friends house was "going out
OL,4,Cwith a bang" before fatal explosion
OL,6,F"My neighbour was in and she said she
OL,7,Fhad never heard anything like it. It
OL,8,Fwas horrendous. By the time we had got
OL,9,Fback here, all hell had broken loose."
OL,11,FShe added: "Twelve months on and
OL,12,Fpeople on the street are no further
OL,13,Fforward with things. It's awful, it
OL,14,Freally is awful."
OL,16,FIf you have been affected by the
OL,17,Fissues in this story, advice and
OL,18,Fsupport can be found on our website.
OL,19,FSamaritans can be contacted 24 hours a
OL,20,Fday, seven days a week on 116 123 or
OL,21,Fat jo@samaritans.org
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1         G7/8
